Wouldn't it be nice if Junit could do all the hard
work and create the
tests for you? 

We've started an open source project to explore that
idea. Obviously
it can't work out every condition. However as a start,
it can generate
junit boundary test conditions and is data driven by
JTestcase.

If you are interested its also hosted on sourceforge 
http://sourceforge.net/projects/spike-test-gen/
